<!-- GENERAL PROVISIONS -->
<div class="section" style="margin-top:16px;">
  <div class="section-title">General Provisions &amp; Limitations</div>
  <div class="provisions-box">
    <p><strong>Coverage Period:</strong> This contract provides dental benefits for the period beginning on the Coverage Start Date and ending on the Coverage End Date shown above, subject to timely premium payment.</p>
    <p><strong>Eligibility:</strong> Coverage extends to all active eligible employees and their enrolled dependents. Newly eligible employees must enroll within 30 days of eligibility or during the annual open enrollment period.</p>
    <p><strong>Dependent Coverage:</strong> Eligible dependents include legal spouse/domestic partner and unmarried dependent children through age 26.</p>
    <p><strong>Waiting Periods:</strong> As specified per plan. New hires may be subject to an initial waiting period before benefits become effective.</p>
    <p><strong>Network Providers:</strong> Services from Delta Dental PPO network providers result in lower out-of-pocket costs. Out-of-network services are covered at a reduced benefit level based on the Maximum Plan Allowance (MPA).</p>
    <p><strong>Coordination of Benefits:</strong> If a covered person has other dental coverage, Delta Dental will coordinate benefits to avoid overpayment.</p>
    <p><strong>Claims Filing:</strong> Claims must be submitted within 12 months of the date of service.</p>
    <p><strong>Termination of Coverage:</strong> Coverage terminates on the last day of the month in which employment ends, unless COBRA or other continuation coverage rights apply.</p>
    <p><strong>Exclusions:</strong> This contract does not cover: cosmetic procedures (unless resulting from accidental injury), experimental treatments, services covered under Workers' Compensation, or duplicate services within the stated frequency limitations.</p>
  </div>
</div>

